abstracts.cdata!:
A five-year technical assistance program
            to finance various studies, including studies for the
            identification and preparation of sufficiently
            well-formulated projects in all sectors for potential
            financing by the Bank Group and other aid agencies, and to
            finance advisory services. The proposed projects are
            expected to have a significant impact on Indonesia's
            socioeconomic problems, with particular emphasis on
            employment creation, fulfillment of basic human needs and
            alleviation of poverty. The proposed credit of $10 million
            would finance up to 85% of each subproject cost. The
            remainder would be provided by the Government through
            budgetary allocations.
